- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with social influence and opinion evolution in online collective behavior. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper involves the development of a quantitative model to predict opinion dynamics. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper discusses the impact of social influence on human judgment revision. 
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is a relevant category as the paper uses a crowdsourced experiment to study social influence and opinion evolution. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible category as the paper deals with human behavior in online collective settings.
